{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.30",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 30 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:1",
      "text": "But now they that are younger than I have me in derision, whose fathers I would have disdained to have set with the dogs of my flock.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:2",
      "text": "Yea, whereto might the strength of their hands profit me, in whom old age was perished?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:3",
      "text": "For want and famine they were solitary; fleeing into the wilderness in former time desolate and waste.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:4",
      "text": "Who cut up mallows by the bushes, and juniper roots for their meat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:5",
      "text": "They were driven forth from among men, (they cried after them as after a thief;)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:6",
      "text": "To dwell in the clifts of the valleys, in caves of the earth, and in the rocks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:7",
      "text": "Among the bushes they brayed; under the nettles they were gathered together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:8",
      "text": "They were children of fools, yea, children of base men: they were viler than the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:9",
      "text": "And now am I their song, yea, I am their byword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:10",
      "text": "They abhor me, they flee far from me, and spare not to spit in my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:11",
      "text": "Because he hath loosed my cord, and afflicted me, they have also let loose the bridle before me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:12",
      "text": "Upon my right hand rise the youth; they push away my feet, and they raise up against me the ways of their destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:13",
      "text": "They mar my path, they set forward my calamity, they have no helper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:14",
      "text": "They came upon me as a wide breaking in of waters: in the desolation they rolled themselves upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:15",
      "text": "Terrors are turned upon me: they pursue my soul as the wind: and my welfare passeth away as a cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:16",
      "text": "And now my soul is poured out upon me; the days of affliction have taken hold upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:17",
      "text": "My bones are pierced in me in the night season: and my sinews take no rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:18",
      "text": "By the great force of my disease is my garment changed: it bindeth me about as the collar of my coat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:19",
      "text": "He hath cast me into the mire, and I am become like dust and ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:20",
      "text": "I cry unto thee, and thou dost not hear me: I stand up, and thou regardest me not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:21",
      "text": "Thou art become cruel to me: with thy strong hand thou opposest thyself against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:22",
      "text": "Thou liftest me up to the wind; thou causest me to ride upon it, and dissolvest my substance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:23",
      "text": "For I know that thou wilt bring me to death, and to the house appointed for all living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:24",
      "text": "Howbeit he will not stretch out his hand to the grave, though they cry in his destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:25",
      "text": "Did not I weep for him that was in trouble? was not my soul grieved for the poor?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:26",
      "text": "When I looked for good, then evil came unto me: and when I waited for light, there came darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:27",
      "text": "My bowels boiled, and rested not: the days of affliction prevented me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:28",
      "text": "I went mourning without the sun: I stood up, and I cried in the congregation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:29",
      "text": "I am a brother to dragons, and a companion to owls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:30",
      "text": "My skin is black upon me, and my bones are burned with heat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.30.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:31",
      "text": "My harp also is turned to mourning, and my organ into the voice of them that weep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
